AnyEvent-Curl-Multi

AnyEvent::Curl::Multi is a fast, event-driven HTTP client based on AnyEvent
and libcurl.  It should be compatible with any event loop that AnyEvent
supports.

For best results, libcurl version 7.21 or later is recommended.

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc AnyEvent::Curl::Multi

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=AnyEvent-Curl-Multi

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/AnyEvent-Curl-Multi

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/AnyEvent-Curl-Multi

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/AnyEvent-Curl-Multi/


